{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all public car parks to have cash and/or card payment options",
        "additional_details": "Not all car users have a working smart phone equipped with the required car parking apps. We believe requiring payment in specific ways discriminates against some users.\r\n \r\nIn addition, phone battery and signal problems make phone payment unreliable.\r\n \r\nCash is preferred by many but if this is not possible then provision of bank card payment should be mandatory.\r\n \r\nIn situations where payment by cash and card is inoperable for any reason then charges for car parking should not be allowed.\r\n \r\nPhone payment should only be an option for those who prefer it, not the only option available.\r\n",
        "background": "To make it law that car parks used by the public must make provision for cash and/or bank card payments, if they are not free.",
